15/09/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- Albanian Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu said his country's peacekeepers would remain in Iraq as long as US forces are there. During an official visit to Washington on Thursday (14 September), Mediu added that Albania is considering boosting its presence in Afghanistan to contribute to the stabilisation process there. He described such international missions as a good opportunity to demonstrate Albanian forces' level of preparedness. 
In other news, Albanian police announced on Thursday that they had uncovered three labs processing hashish. One was in Patos, a small town some 5km from Fier, while the others were near Vlora. (Albanian News - 15/09/06)
